Jul 21 2009 	Totally alright and I would stay there again	I've stayed in this hotel 4-5 times in the past 2,5 years, have stayed there for 1, 2 and 4 weeks and I have to say that I'm quite happy with it and would try booking it for my next trip to Dubai as well.I'm really not sure where all those negative revies are coming from I've had ONLY 2 unpleasant occasions:1. First time they were supposed to pick me up from the airport but it tokk me forever to go thought passport control so there was noone at the airport arrivals waiting for me. I called the hotel and they told me to take any taxi and they'll pay the bill, which they really did.2. Some other time I arranged (free) transfer back to the aiport with them but it was some odd time in the middle of the night for a red-eye flight so when I checked out there was no transportation waiting. However, the receptionist solved it and 15min later I had my transfer.Well, 2 other slight negative is that they have one very serious-faced waitress (hostess?) in the breakfast restaurant. I think she could act a bit more friendly. Then they also have one rather annoying doorman who grabs your bag from your hands every single time you show up at the entrance, even if they are so small that there is obviously no need for help. A tip beggar, really, kind of annoying.I NEVER had any problems witch check-in or booking or them ignoring my e-mails, quite the opposite: I need visa to enter Dubai (arranged by the hotel) and sometimes my requests are very confusing and changing: my travel dates change, or are pending, or my required visa type changes, or I need to split/combine the bookings.. So, every single time the reply very fast, with all the info I'm asking, with great willigness to jump through all the hoops with all my messy requests, making sure someone else picks up my case immediately if the initial person goes on holiday etc, their &quot;visa manager&quot; always deals with me personally, in e-mails and in person, there's always a cold welcome drink upon arrival etc.Moreover, they are flexible with my check-out times (check out at 9pm with no extra charge), always fresh flowers in my room (with some hotel chocolates and flower petals on my bed), always complimentary bottle of water (not just the first one). Another time they picked up my additional visa charge (charged by coressponding government authorities) despite the screw-up that caused the charge was from my side AND still gave me late check out option at no extra charge...Anyways, my rooms are always decent size, clean, comfortable and well equipped, the staff is very nice and helpful (except for that one serious waitress and that one beggar doorman)... Someone complained about no iron in the room, no alcohol in the hotel and about construction/ugly view. Well, it is Dubai, you know. Meaning, construction everywhere and absence of alcohol - is NORMAL for that city. Sure, there are are hotels with lovely views and/or no construction nearby but those would be in a different price category. Given reality of Dubai as whole Coral Deira has TOTALLY NORMAL price/value ratio.As for the iron, once again - it's Dubai. &quot;Outsourcing&quot; that sort of work is so affordable and widely spread here that noone would imagine that a 4*-5* hotel guest would even consider doing it himself.Location - close to the airport, a couple of decent malls and a handful of nice restaurants. I agree that it's not in the best spot for visiting the main attractions of contemporary Dubai, all the westernized, brand new skyscrapers and all that jazz. But if you want to get a feel of more &quot;real&quot; Dubai, more authentic - and delicious and cheap! -restaurants - then the location is excellent.I'm happy with the hotel and the price, would recommend it and would stay there again.	
